{"key":"post-9719800","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9719800</id>\n<content>If you'll build a shotgun terrarium by the tek, you'll have upper 90% humidity AND good air exchange.&amp;nbsp; You're trying to fix what isn't broken.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Never try to avoid misting.&amp;nbsp; Since evaporation of moisture from the substrate is the number 1 pinning trigger, you must mist to replace what evaporates.&amp;nbsp; If you get the substrate soggy, it will perform poorly if at all.&amp;nbsp; Fresh air causes evaporation, and the shotgun gives you the optimum growing environment.&amp;nbsp; Nothing is labor free.&amp;nbsp; You must mist as your cakes or other substrate dries, to get good results.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9720931</next>\n<prev>9718639</prev>\n<first>9686519</first>\n<last>9721318</last>\n<when>1233547019</when>\n<utime>02/02/09 05:56 AM</utime>\n</post>"}